From fa797a0993ebfdad17b7291ed93454e1b72949db Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Thomas Debesse <dev@illwieckz.net>
Date: Sun, 19 Jul 2026 00:00:58 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] gdb/gdbserver/linux-x86-low.c: fix ps_get_thread_area()
 signature
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Fix:

linux-x86-low.c:219:1: error: conflicting types for ‘ps_get_thread_area’; have ‘ps_err_e(const struct ps_prochandle *, lwpid_t,  int,  void **)’ {aka ‘ps_err_e(const struct ps_prochandle *, int,  int,  void **)’}
  219 | ps_get_thread_area (const struct ps_prochandle *ph,
      | ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
In file included from gdb_proc_service.h:25,
                 from linux-low.h:23,
                 from linux-x86-low.c:25:
/usr/include/proc_service.h:72:17: note: previous declaration of ‘ps_get_thread_area’ with type ‘ps_err_e(struct ps_prochandle *, lwpid_t,  int,  void **)’ {aka ‘ps_err_e(struct ps_prochandle *, int,  int,  void **)’}
   72 | extern ps_err_e ps_get_thread_area (struct ps_prochandle *,
---
 gdb/gdbserver/linux-x86-low.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/gdb/gdbserver/linux-x86-low.c b/gdb/gdbserver/linux-x86-low.c
index e8505bf0..ff45d534 100644
--- a/gdb/gdbserver/linux-x86-low.c
+++ b/gdb/gdbserver/linux-x86-low.c
@@ -216,7 +216,7 @@ is_64bit_tdesc (void)
 /* Called by libthread_db.  */
 
 ps_err_e
-ps_get_thread_area (const struct ps_prochandle *ph,
+ps_get_thread_area (struct ps_prochandle *ph,
 		    lwpid_t lwpid, int idx, void **base)
 {
 #ifdef __x86_64__
-- 
2.43.0

